issue.title: Move executor scripts which exist only in “lmnet/executor”

repository.name: blueoil
repository.description: Bring Deep Learning to small devices

issue.body:
Related to #746 .

This PR moves executor scripts which exist only in `lmnet/executor` to `blueoil/cmd`. This change has no conflicts with the existing scripts in `blueoil/cmd`. So the target scripts are simply moved. Paths in code, comments and docs which point the target scripts are updated.

Target scripts:
- build_tfds.py
- convert_weight_from_darknet.py (will be deleted: #781)
- evaluate.py
- export.py
- measure_latency.py
- output_event.py
- profile_model.py
- profile_template.md
- tune_ray.py

issue.title: Unify 2 types of config format into lmnet config

repository.name: blueoil
repository.description: Bring Deep Learning to small devices

issue.body:
## Overview
This PR is preparation for moving `train.py` and `predict.py` from `lmnet/executor` to `blueoil/cmd` (https://github.com/blue-oil/blueoil/issues/746). This PR aims for throwing blueoil config away and unifying 2 types of config format into lmnet config.

### Important changes
`init.py` is updated to generate lmnet config instead of blueoil config. `generate_lmnet_config.py` and config template files are updated a little according to this change. `train.py` is also updated to accept lmnet config.
- `blueoil/cmd/init.py`
- `blueoil/cmd/train.py`
- `blueoil/generate_lmnet_config.py`
- `blueoil/templates/lmnet/classification.tpl.py`
- `blueoil/templates/lmnet/object_detection.tpl.py`
- `blueoil/templates/lmnet/semantic_segmentation.tpl.py`

### E2E test updates
The E2E test code is also updated according to config format updates. The config files for blueoil test are removed and the test scripts are updated to generate them on-the-fly.
- `tests/e2e/conftest.py`
- `tests/e2e/test_classification.py`
- `tests/e2e/test_keypoint_detection.py`
- `tests/e2e/test_object_detection.py`
- `tests/e2e/test_semantic_segmentation.py`
- `tests/fixtures/configs/*.yaml` (deleted)

issue.title: Move train.py and predict.py from lmnet/executor to blueoil/cmd

repository.name: blueoil
repository.description: Bring Deep Learning to small devices

issue.body:
## What this patch does to fix the issue.
- Removed `train.py` and `predict.py` in `blueoil/cmd` (https://github.com/blue-oil/blueoil/commit/d892888aff9e3ad6ef6ca79059b9db8fea0ff603)
- Moved `train.py` and `predict.py` from `lmnet/executor` to `blueoil/cmd` (https://github.com/blue-oil/blueoil/commit/fd9f550eb8e92f870b28664fe7c57848e0c54761)
- Update `train.py` and `predict.py` to be callable as blueoil commands (https://github.com/blue-oil/blueoil/commit/0246fdf21b7ec9f4c5abc9910353cbf3761819c2)

This PR looks big but most of the changes are just copied. Maybe it's easier to check each commit one by one than checking the whole changes.

## Link to any relevant issues or pull requests.
This PR will close https://github.com/blue-oil/blueoil/issues/746 .
